<FONT SIZE=6>Canadian Centre on Substance Abuse<FONT SIZE=4> is a non-profit organization working to minimize the harm associated with the use of 
alcohol, tobacco and other drugs.  The Centre was created in 1988 under <A HREF="cds.htm">Canada's Drug Strategy</A>.<FONT SIZE=3>
<P>
